Police confiscate the the large sum of money at Stockport border. JOHANNESBURG - Police on Wednesday arrested a man at the Stockport border in possession of an undeclared sum of money amounting to R1,75-million. "When searching his rented vehicle, police discovered a bag full of banknotes in the boot," said police spokesperson, Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo. READ: MTN batteries worth R1-million recovered in Pretoria Police assigned to the border post were conducting routine duties when they stopped him. He was attempting to cross the border into Botswana. The 24-year-old suspect will appear at the Lephalale Magistrate’s Court on Thursday on money laundering charges.